courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of courses, students will be able to
1. obtain a grasp of curriculum design models;
2. identify factors influencing curriculum and instructional design;
3. comprehend the different stages of curriculum development;
4. understand and principles and key concepts underpinning a curriculum design

學生在完成此科目後能
1. 掌握不同的課程設計模式;
2. 辨別出影響課程與教學設計的因素;
3. 了解課程發展的不同階段;
4. 明白課程設計的原則及概念。

At the end of this course, students will be able to:

* understand the complexity of environmental issues as an interplay between science, politics, values, economy, education and social development;

* critically understand key environmental issues at both local and global levels;

* actively participate in the discourse and actions concerning environmental issues;

* recognize different approaches to environmental education and critically analyze their strengths and constraints;

* understand the relations between environmental education and cultural differences;

* actively participate in environmental education both inside and outside the school systems;

* appreciate and to live an environmentally-friendly lifestyle

By the end of this course, students will be able to:
1. recognize the key features of education in different periods in HK ;
2. explain the relations between the social development and the educational changes in HK ;
3. reflect upon the functions of education in the contexts of Hong Kong society.

By the end of the course, participants will:

1. Illustrate how the social and political environment affect the change of models in the development of curriculum in Hong Kong;
2. Use civic education or other subjects as an example to list the change of curriculum model from the past to future;
3. Identify the definition and principles of school-based curriculum and construct a frame work for analysis;
4. Identify the situational features, core values, concepts and characteristics of different cases based on own analytical framework;
5. Analyze curriculum model and factors that affect the development and implementation of the model in case study;
6. Analyze main difficulties in sustainable development and implementation of different cases; and
7. Evaluate the relationship among school-based curriculum, social and political changes in Hong Kong.

學員完成本科後將能夠：

1. 闡述香港社會和政治環境變遷如何影響課程發展模式的改變；
2. 以公民教育或其他科目為例，列舉現今課程與過往課程模式的改變；
3. 認出「校本課程」定義、原理，並建立分析框架；
4. 利用分析框架，認出各個案的情境特徵、核心價值、概念和設計特色；
5. 分析個案的課程模式及其發展和實施的影響因素；
6. 分析個案的可持續性發展與實施的主要困難；
7. 評析一項校本課程與香港的社會和政治環境變遷的可能關係。

By the end of the course, students will be able to:

1. demonstrate competence and broad understanding of the professional standards and basic legal knowledge for teachers in Hong Kong;

2. identify moral dilemmas facing teachers and make responsible decisions by considering different ethical perspectives, and finding the best possible way forward for all stakeholders;

3. act conscientiously with regard to the professional standards and the law, and collaborate ethically and competently in multi-disciplinary and multi-cultural teams; and

4. develop a commitment to the teaching profession and reflect on the professional standards in individual practices.

By the end of this course, students will be able to:
1. understand recent educational reforms and their impacts on Hong Kong’s education system;
2. analyze influential factors of the development of teaching profession;
3. examine teachers’ role to key aspects of changes required under reform contexts;
4. devise an individualized professional development plan within school contexts;
5. able to reflect on and improve their individual practices.

By the end of this course, students will be able to:

(1) develop a critical understanding of the place of values in moral education and citizenship education;
(2) understand and appreciate some important concepts related to moral, values and citizenship education;
(3) apply these important concepts to understanding and evaluating Hong Kong situations.

(4) be able to develop pedagogies related to moral, values and citizenship education possibly in the form of case studies or lesson plans.

By the end of this course, students will be able to:

(1) develop a critical awareness of personal attitudes towards and beliefs in life and death;

(2) gain a critical understanding of various perspectives on meaning pertaining to life and death;

(3) possess a positive attitude towards life and essential skills in tacking negative life incidents and death issues;

(4) apply the learned knowledge, attitude, and skills to build connections with their future pupils to create a supportive safety net for them in preventing suicidal behaviours;

(5) engage in continuing professional development as competent teachers for Life and Death Education in their future school teaching.

