By the end of this course, students will be able to:
1. understand various pedagogical and technological conceptions related to IT in education;
2. gain practical knowledge and skills in developing multimedia and online resources for educational use;
3. integrate multimedia and eLearning elements into the process of learning and teaching;
4. apply WebQuest in their subjects of teaching;
5. enhance their information literacy.

By the end of this course, students will be able to:
1. gain pedagogical knowledge and technological skills related to e-Learning;
2. apply various e-Learning strategies to support face-to-face teaching and self-directed learning;
3. analyse and evaluate the strengths and weaknesses of various e-Learning strategies with respect to different educational contexts;
4. innovate and design inside-/ outside-the-classroom e-Learning activities and resources that address different educational needs and challenges in schools;
5. realize the importance of collaboration in the learning process with sharpened collaboration skills.

By the end of this course, students will be able to:
1. state the characteristics and purposes of the selected conceptual and theoretical models on classroom management and school discipline;
2. identify the factors affecting the positive student-teacher relationship development in the classroom and in school;
3. be aware of personal strengths and limitations as a teacher in the subject of classroom management;
4. acquire skills to build a strong and positive student-teacher rapport as well as to promote an environment of optimal learning in the classroom; and
5. develop effective strategies to promote self-discipline and positive behaviors among primary students.
